textBody:
ICI or Ici may refer to:

Media

* Ici Radio-Canada, branding of Radio-Canada, the French language service of the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation beginning in 2013
* ICI (TV channel), full name International Channel/Canal International, Montreal ethnic / multicultural television channel, a.k.a. CFHD-DT
* Ici (magazine), an alternative French language weekly newspaper in Montreal, Canada, now defunct
* International Channel/Canal International, an ethnic television station in Montreal, Quebec, Canada known legally as CFHD-DT

Companies and organisations

* ICI Homes, a homebuilder in Florida, United States
* Imperial Chemical Industries, former British chemicals company
* Independent Curators International, a non-profit headquartered in New York City
* Indian Concrete Institute
* Indian Citation Index, an online bibliographic database containing abstracts and citations/references from academic journals
* Institute of Cultural Inquiry, an international organization functioning as a think-tank for artists
* Investment Company Institute, an American investment company trade organization
* Istanbul Cooperation Initiative, an initiative launched during NATO's 2004 Istanbul Summit
* International Compact with Iraq

Other uses

* Inter Carrier Interface, a transport protocol (IANA port 2200) for use with SMDS
* Interactive Compilation Interface, transforms production compilers into research toolsets
* Intracervical Insemination
* ICI programming language, a computer programming language developed in 1992
